        "title": "Add Gateway system.run MXC runtime E2E proof",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nPR3 for #784. This adds a focused runtime proof for the real Gateway path:\n\nGateway -> node.invoke -> Windows node -> system.run -> MXC process containment.\n\nThis is intentionally stacked after #786. The PR3-only commit is 8f55454 (`test: prove gateway system.run through MXC sandbox`). A focused compare for the PR3 delta is:\nhttps://github.com/TheAngryPit/openclaw-windows-node/compare/feature/mxc-26200-sdk-0-7-validation...feature/gateway-system-run-mxc-e2e\n\n## What changed\n\n- Adds `RealGateway_SystemRun_ExecutesThroughWindowsNodeMxcSandbox` to the E2E setup suite.\n- The test provisions a fresh WSL Gateway, starts an isolated tray instance, sets a local exec approval through MCP, invokes `system.run` through `openclaw gateway call node.invoke`, and verifies MXC diagnostics in the tray log.\n- Documents the focused runtime proof command and required evidence markers in `docs/WINDOWS_NODE_TESTING.md`.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `./build.ps1` passed.\n- `dotnet test ./tests/OpenClaw.Shared.Tests/OpenClaw.Shared.Tests.csproj --no-restore` passed: 2291 passed, 29 skipped, 0 failed.\n- `dotnet test ./tests/OpenClaw.Tray.Tests/OpenClaw.Tray.Tests.csproj --no-restore` passed: 1088 passed, 0 failed, using isolated temp APPDATA/LOCALAPPDATA and a preseeded temp device identity to avoid touching real user settings.\n- Focused runtime E2E passed: `RealGateway_SystemRun_ExecutesThroughWindowsNodeMxcSandbox`, 1 passed in 3.02 min.\n- Runtime proof markers observed: `OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_SYSTEM_RUN_MXC_OK`, `executor=mxc-direct-appc`, `contained=True`, `shell=cmd`, `exitCode=0`, `containment=mxc`.\n- `git diff --check` passed for the PR3 files.\n- `openclaw-autoreview` clean: no accepted/actionable findings, reviewed in a clean temporary clone scoped to the PR3 two-file delta.\n\n## Notes\n\nThis proves the Gateway/Windows-node/MXC runtime path. It does not claim proof of the installed Windows Companion UI path.\n\nRefs #784\nStacked after #786\n",
